-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - July 21
-- 
-- Mon Jul 21, 2014 02:31AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, July 21 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Monday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- Boiko Borisov, leader of centre-right GERB party, the most likely winner in October polls, pledged to change the management of Bulgarian Central Bank if elected. (Trud, Presa, 24 Chasa) -- A new poll show two-thirds of Bulgarians do not support a state bailout and coverage of all deposits in Corporate Commercial Bank <6C9.BB>, anew poll by independent AFIS pollster showed. (Sega, Standart, 24 Chasa) SEGA - The government plans to gradually help over 2,000 asylum seekers leave its refugee camps and help them find work and shelter in the country, a new strategy showed.